People with #disability can be more likely to experience #abuse due to a range of factors, including reliance on other people for personal care, mobility and income. Our website contains information for people with disability to get support. https://t.co/Z0tKpFjujY

#Daisy is the free 1800RESPECT app that provides information about support services in your area. The free, easy to use app is often recommended to those impacted by #domesticviolence by sector professionals. Find out more on our website. https://t.co/NeOXuzTh8u

There are many ways to support a loved one who is experiencing #financialabuse, and #1800RESPECT can assist with advice for those in a #support role. Call 1800 737 732 or visit our website: https://t.co/xtkP3EroA3

A #safetyplan for a person with #disability needs to be developed with a support service. Issues such as communication difficulties or special care requirements can mean that extra planning and support are needed. Learn more on our website: https://t.co/LgSs3YW0Mj

The #Disability Support Toolkit has been developed to provide #sexualassault, #domesticviolence and disability frontline workers with resources to assist people who have experienced violence and abuse. https://t.co/Fk4VcuwdOQ

We invite you to subscribe to our Workers and Professionals newsletter. Updates on the #1800RESPECT service, #DVSA sector information, upcoming #conferences and more are delivered quarterly to your inbox. Winter edition out soon. Sign up via our website. https://t.co/ZmQVSrS4Nx

For many people with #disability, recognising that what they are experiencing is #abuse is a significant issue. It can be made worse by limited access to information. Our website has information on recognising forms of violence and how to access support. https://t.co/8p0CXl2mqn
